Package jetbrains.mps.typechecking.backend

Class TypecheckingSessionHandler

  • java.lang.Object
    • jetbrains.mps.typechecking.backend.TypecheckingSessionHandler
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    TypecheckingComputations
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    TypecheckingFacade
    public abstract class TypecheckingSessionHandler
extends Object
implements TypecheckingComputations
    Provides an interface for manipulating typechecking sessions. The method requestNewSession(Flags) can be called by clients wishing to start a new typechecking session with specific features. The session will be managed by this component, but the client is free to call TypecheckingSessionImpl.release() at any time to signal that the session is no longer required.

      • requestNewSession

        @NotNull
public final TypecheckingSession.Handle requestNewSession​(@NotNull
                                                          TypecheckingSession.Flags flags)
        Requests that a new session is initiated with provided flags. All typechecking queries in this context are to be run via this session, which forwards them to its participants, until the session is released. See TypecheckingFacade.getFromContext() for the discussion of what context is.
